<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="520" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,367,717]" pageId="5" pageNumber="520">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,267,476,501]" pageId="5" pageNumber="520">Remarks.</emphasis>
From phylogenetic analyses, Bohlen 
<emphasis box="[687,743,476,501]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="520">et al.</emphasis>
(2011) proposed that there are three major lineages within the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Blyth" authorityYear="1860" box="[234,315,513,536]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cobitidae" genus="Pangio" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageId="5" pageNumber="520" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[234,315,513,536]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="520">Pangio</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, namely the 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Kottelat &amp; Lim" authorityYear="1993" box="[491,614,511,536]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cobitidae" genus="Pangio" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageId="5" pageNumber="520" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="anguillaris">
<emphasis box="[491,614,511,536]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="520">anguillaris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
lineage,the 
<emphasis box="[772,878,511,536]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="520">shelfordii</emphasis>
lineage and the 
<emphasis box="[1104,1269,511,536]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="520">kuhlii -oblonga</emphasis>
lineage. The 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Kottelat &amp; Lim" authorityYear="1993" box="[151,274,548,573]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cobitidae" genus="Pangio" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageId="5" pageNumber="520" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="anguillaris">
<emphasis box="[151,274,548,573]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="520">anguillaris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
-lineage comprise 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Kottelat &amp; Lim" authorityYear="1993" box="[485,637,548,573]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cobitidae" genus="Pangio" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageId="5" pageNumber="520" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="anguillaris">
<emphasis box="[485,637,548,573]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="520">P. anguillaris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Tan &amp; Kottelat" authorityYear="2009" box="[653,781,548,573]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cobitidae" genus="Pangio" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageId="5" pageNumber="520" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="bitaimac">
<emphasis box="[653,781,548,573]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="520">P. bitaimac</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Perugia" baseAuthorityYear="1892" box="[797,899,548,573]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cobitidae" genus="Pangio" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageId="5" pageNumber="520" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="doriae">
<emphasis box="[797,899,548,573]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="520">P. doriae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Britz &amp; Maclaine" authorityYear="2007" box="[958,1154,548,573]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cobitidae" genus="Pangio" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageId="5" pageNumber="520" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="lumbriciformis">
<emphasis box="[958,1154,548,573]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="520">P. lumbriciformis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. They hypothesized that phylogenetic pattern of the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Blyth" authorityYear="1860" box="[535,616,585,608]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cobitidae" genus="Pangio" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageId="5" pageNumber="520" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[535,616,585,608]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="520">Pangio</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was the result of a vicariance event that separated the common ancestor into Bornean and Peninsular Malaysian sub-groups. Since the 
<typeStatus box="[875,923,621,645]" pageId="5" pageNumber="520">type</typeStatus>
locality 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Kottelat &amp; Lim" authorityYear="1993" box="[1027,1181,620,645]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cobitidae" genus="Pangio" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageId="5" pageNumber="520" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="anguillaris">
<emphasis box="[1027,1181,620,645]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="520">P. anguillaris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is Kapuas in Borneo, specimens recorded in Peninsular 
<collectingCountry box="[533,639,655,680]" name="Malaysia" pageId="5" pageNumber="520">Malaysia</collectingCountry>
, the Chao Phraya and the lower Mekong basins may be confused under this name. We recognize that there may be a possible taxonomic revision in the future.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
